WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.467 --> 00:00:04.868
♪♪

00:00:04.868 --> 00:00:08.767
Narrator:
FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS,
WE'VE USED BELLS TO MAKE NOISE.

00:00:08.767 --> 00:00:10.934
THE CONCEPT BEHIND THEM
IS SIMPLE.

00:00:10.934 --> 00:00:13.434
A CLAPPER OR HAMMER
STRIKES THE BELL WALL,

00:00:13.434 --> 00:00:16.467
CREATING VIBRATIONS
THAT DISTURB THE AIR.

00:00:16.467 --> 00:00:19.434
THE DISTURBANCE CAUSES
THE RINGING SOUND.

00:00:19.434 --> 00:00:23.767
IT'S NOT HIGH TECH,
BUT IT CAN BE HIGH-PITCHED.

00:00:23.767 --> 00:00:25.367
[ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS ]

00:00:25.367 --> 00:00:27.934
EVERY BELL HAS
A DISTINCTIVE RING,

00:00:27.934 --> 00:00:30.400
FROM THE FESTIVE JINGLE
OF SLEIGH BELLS

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:32.267
TO THE CLANG OF THE BOXING BELL

00:00:32.267 --> 00:00:35.567
THAT MARKS
THE BEGINNING OF A FIGHT.

00:00:35.567 --> 00:00:40.601
EVEN THE COW BELL HAS A SOUND
THAT'S NOT QUITE LIKE ANY OTHER.

00:00:40.601 --> 00:00:43.367
THE BELL'S SHAPE AND THE
MATERIAL IT'S MADE FROM

00:00:43.367 --> 00:00:45.367
AFFECT THE RING'S PITCH.

00:00:45.367 --> 00:00:47.601
TO MAKE A COW BELL,
AN ASSEMBLER USES

00:00:47.601 --> 00:00:51.567
TWO FLARED STEEL COMPONENTS
TO FORM A CONE.

00:00:51.567 --> 00:00:54.968
HE INSERTS A HANDLE BETWEEN
THE TWO PARTS AT THE TOP...

00:00:54.968 --> 00:00:56.634
♪♪

00:00:56.634 --> 00:00:58.901
AND WELDS THE SEAMS
OF THE BELL SHELL

00:00:58.901 --> 00:01:00.834
TO HOLD THE TWO PARTS TOGETHER.

00:01:00.834 --> 00:01:04.701
♪♪

00:01:04.701 --> 00:01:08.634
THEN, HE WELDS THE HANDLE
TO THE COW-BELL BODY.

00:01:08.634 --> 00:01:10.801
THE HANDLE CONTAINS A SMALL LOOP

00:01:10.801 --> 00:01:15.701
THAT EXTENDS INSIDE THE BELL
BODY TO HOLD THE CLAPPER.

00:01:15.701 --> 00:01:18.300
THIS STRIP OF STEEL IS
ABOUT TO BE TRANSFORMED

00:01:18.300 --> 00:01:21.501
INTO SLEIGH BELLS.

00:01:21.501 --> 00:01:23.634
AN UPPER DIE FORCES
THE STEEL STRIP

00:01:23.634 --> 00:01:26.767
INTO DIES ON A ROTATING PLATTER.

00:01:26.767 --> 00:01:28.901
THE DIES FORM
THE METAL INTO A SHAPE

00:01:28.901 --> 00:01:32.868
THAT RESEMBLES AN OPEN FLOWER.

00:01:32.868 --> 00:01:36.601
BALL BEARINGS FUNNEL
INTO A CHUTE.

00:01:36.601 --> 00:01:39.901
THE BALL BEARINGS LAND IN THE
OPEN FLOWERS ON THE PLATTER.

00:01:39.901 --> 00:01:42.634
♪♪

00:01:42.634 --> 00:01:45.467
THE UPPER DIE CLOSES
THE PETALS OF THE FLOWER,

00:01:45.467 --> 00:01:47.968
CREATING A ROUND SLEIGH BELL.

00:01:47.968 --> 00:01:52.567
THE RATTLE OF THE INTERIOR BALL
BEARING WILL CREATE THE SOUND.

00:01:52.567 --> 00:01:56.567
A DEVICE POPS THE BELL
OUT OF THE DIE

00:01:56.567 --> 00:01:58.767
AND THE SLEIGH BELLS FALL
INTO A BIN.

00:01:58.767 --> 00:02:00.601
♪♪

00:02:00.601 --> 00:02:03.400
ONCE THE SLEIGH BELLS
ARE PLATED WITH NICKEL,

00:02:03.400 --> 00:02:04.968
THEY ARE READY FOR RATTLING.

00:02:04.968 --> 00:02:07.701
♪♪

00:02:07.701 --> 00:02:12.100
AT ANOTHER STATION, A BOXING
BELL BEGINS TO TAKE SHAPE.

00:02:12.100 --> 00:02:14.801
AN ASSEMBLER TRANSFERS
THE BELL TO A PUNCH

00:02:14.801 --> 00:02:16.300
THAT CUTS A HOLE IN THE CENTER.

00:02:16.300 --> 00:02:18.167
THE PUNCH FORCES IT
ONTO A FORM

00:02:18.167 --> 00:02:22.200
THAT CONTOURS
THE AREA AROUND THE HOLE.

00:02:22.200 --> 00:02:26.667
OIL KEEPS THE METAL LUBRICATED
AS IT'S FORMING.

00:02:26.667 --> 00:02:29.267
THE GONGS TUMBLE AROUND
IN A MACHINE

00:02:29.267 --> 00:02:33.501
WITH VIBRATING CERAMIC STONES,
DETERGENT, AND WATER.

00:02:33.501 --> 00:02:36.734
♪♪

00:02:36.734 --> 00:02:40.868
THE STONES SCRUB OFF THE OIL
AND RUB OFF ROUGH EDGES.

00:02:40.868 --> 00:02:42.400
AFTER ABOUT 10 MINUTES,

00:02:42.400 --> 00:02:45.367
THE GONGS EMERGE,
SMOOTH AND CLEAN.

00:02:45.367 --> 00:02:48.300
THEY LAND IN THE TUB
OF GROUND CORN COBS.

00:02:48.300 --> 00:02:51.100
THE CORN ABSORBS
ANY RESIDUAL WATER

00:02:51.100 --> 00:02:54.968
AS IT PULSATES IN THIS
VIBRATORY MACHINE.

00:02:54.968 --> 00:02:59.534
A TECHNICIAN PLACES
THE GONGS IN AN OVEN.

00:02:59.534 --> 00:03:01.133
THIS HEAT TREATMENT REARRANGES

00:03:01.133 --> 00:03:04.367
THE CRYSTALLINE STRUCTURES
OF THE STEEL AND HARDENS IT.

00:03:04.367 --> 00:03:06.200
♪♪

00:03:06.200 --> 00:03:08.133
MAKING THE STEEL MORE RESILIENT

00:03:08.133 --> 00:03:11.601
WILL ALSO MAKE THE GONG SOUND
MORE RESONANT WHEN STRUCK.

00:03:11.601 --> 00:03:16.734
♪♪

00:03:16.734 --> 00:03:19.300
THE GONGS ARE SPRAYED
WITH A POWDER COATING.

00:03:19.300 --> 00:03:21.467
WHEN BAKED ON,
THE POWDER PARTICLES

00:03:21.467 --> 00:03:24.234
WILL FORM A PROTECTIVE SKIN
ON THE METAL

00:03:24.234 --> 00:03:27.067
AND PROVIDE THE GONGS
WITH A UNIFORM FINISH.

00:03:27.067 --> 00:03:29.701
♪♪

00:03:29.701 --> 00:03:32.501
A POWDER COAT IS SPRAYED
ON THE BELL'S BASEPLATE

00:03:32.501 --> 00:03:37.567
AND AN ADHESIVE-BACKED COMPANY
LOGO IS APPLIED TO THE BACK.

00:03:37.567 --> 00:03:39.467
POSTS HAVE BEEN INSTALLED
ON THE FRONT

00:03:39.467 --> 00:03:41.901
FOR ASSEMBLING THE OTHER PARTS:

00:03:41.901 --> 00:03:44.601
A BRASS LEVER FOR OPERATING
THE BELL HAMMER

00:03:44.601 --> 00:03:48.701
AND THE MECHANISM THAT WILL
SWING IT, CALLED A DOG.

00:03:48.701 --> 00:03:52.634
THE ASSEMBLER RIVETS
THE DOG TO THE LEVER

00:03:52.634 --> 00:03:56.701
AND HOOKS ONE END OF A SPRING
TO THE MECHANISM.

00:03:56.701 --> 00:03:58.968
HE FASTENS ANOTHER SPRING
TO THE HAMMER

00:03:58.968 --> 00:04:02.434
AND THEN HOOKS THE END
TO THE BASEPLATE.

00:04:02.434 --> 00:04:04.767
HE INSTALLS THE HAMMER
ON ONE OF THE POSTS.

00:04:04.767 --> 00:04:07.567
♪♪

00:04:07.567 --> 00:04:11.367
USING A PUSH NUT, HE SECURES
THE HAMMER TO THE POST.

00:04:11.367 --> 00:04:15.868
♪♪

00:04:15.868 --> 00:04:18.267
HE HOOKS THE LEVER SPRING
ON THE BASEPLATE

00:04:18.267 --> 00:04:23.167
AND SLIDES THE LEVER ONTO A POST
JUST UNDER THE HAMMER.

00:04:23.167 --> 00:04:26.033
ANOTHER PUSH NUT LOCKS
THE LEVER IN PLACE.

00:04:26.033 --> 00:04:28.367
♪♪

00:04:28.367 --> 00:04:31.868
THE ASSEMBLER PULLS THE LEVER,
EXAMINING THE MOVEMENT,

00:04:31.868 --> 00:04:33.634
ADJUSTING ACCORDINGLY.

00:04:33.634 --> 00:04:39.000
♪♪

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:42.133
HE NOW ADDS THE GONG,
ALIGNING THE CENTER HOLE

00:04:42.133 --> 00:04:45.234
TO THE THREADED POST
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE BACKPLATE.

00:04:45.234 --> 00:04:48.868
♪♪

00:04:48.868 --> 00:04:52.667
HE SCREWS ON A FASTENER
TO HOLD THE GONG IN PLACE.

00:04:52.667 --> 00:04:55.000
HE PULLS THE LEVER
TO CONFIRM THAT THE HAMMER

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:57.234
HITS THE GONG
AND MAKES A NOISE.

00:04:57.234 --> 00:05:01.000
♪♪

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:02.868
[ DING ]
FINALLY, THIS BOXING BELL

00:05:02.868 --> 00:05:04.367
IS NOW READY FOR THE RING.

00:05:04.367 --> 00:05:06.501
[ DING ]

00:05:06.501 --> 00:05:07.934
♪♪

